#### Q38. Which code block results in an array `b` containing the mean values of each array within `C`?

- %OPTION% .

```
b = zeros(1, size(C, 2));
for i_C = 1:size(C, 2)
    b(i_C) = mean(C(i_C));
end
```

- %OPTION% .
      `b = cellfun(@mean, C);`
- %OPTION% .

```
b = zeros(1, size(C, 1));
for i_C = 1:size(C, 1)
    b(i_C) = mean(C{i_C}(:));
end
```

- %OPTION% .
      `b = cellfun(@(m) mean(m(:)), C)`

